<div class="topic">
      <h3>The Form Element </h3>
        <p>The Form element is used to group input in a page as one form. Page can contain one or more forms</p>
        <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">form</span>></span><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">/form</span>></span>
</pre>
</div>

<div class="topic">
      <h3>The Input Element </h3>
        <p>The input elements famliy enables us to get the user input while applying some rules on it. </p>
        <p>The rule is determined using the type attribute of the input element</p>
        <p>Some types for example are: text, password, number, submit etc.</p>

        <p> you can find all the list <a href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input'>here</a></p>
        <p>For example the code below will generate a login screen:</p>
        <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">form</span>></span>
UserName: <span style="color:#e0c589">&lt;<span style="color:#e0c589">input</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">type</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">'text'</span> /></span> <span style="color:#e0c589">&lt;<span style="color:#e0c589">br</span>></span>
Password: <span style="color:#e0c589">&lt;<span style="color:#e0c589">input</span> <span style="color:#e0c589">type</span>=<span style="color:#65b042">'password'</span> /></span> <span style="color:#e0c589">&lt;<span style="color:#e0c589">br</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">form</span>></span>
</pre>
</pre>
<p> Result: </p>
<div style="border-style:solid;  border-radius: 4px;">
<form>
UserName: <input type='text' /> <br>
Password: <input type='password' /> <br>
</form>
</div>
</div>

